{{Use Australian English|date=August 2015}}
The '''Darwin International Guitar Festival''' is held once every two years at the [[Charles Darwin University]], [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]], [[Northern Territory]], [[Australia]].<ref>[http://www.cdu.edu.au/community/darwinguitarfestival.html Seventh Darwin International Guitar Festival]</ref> The festival attracts many Australian guitarists<ref>http://www.musicfestivalsaustralia.com/Darwin-International-Guitar-Festival.html</ref> including [[Karin Schaupp]],<ref>http://www.modernguitars.com/archives/000938.html</ref> [[Saffire (music)|Saffire]], and [[Slava Grigoryan]]. Many international stars, such as [[John Williams (guitarist)|John Williams]], also attend.

Australian composers such as [[Richard Charlton (composer)|Richard Charlton]], [[Peter Sculthorpe]] and [[Nicholas Routley]] are also features of the festival.

