{{Infobox person |name=Dolores Della Penna |image= |birth_name= |birth_date={{birth date|1954|12|13}} |birth_place= |death_date=July 12, 1972 (aged 17) |death_place= [[Kensington|Kensington, Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania, U.S. |death_cause=[[Dismemberment]] |body_discovered= |resting_place= |nationality= American |occupation= Student |known_for= Murder victim |image_caption= }}
'''Dolores Della Penna''' (December 13, 1954 – July 12, 1972) was a school girl from [[Philadelphia]] who was [[torture]]d, murdered by dismemberment, and [[Decapitation|beheaded]] in the [[Kensington, Philadelphia|Kensington]] neighborhood in July, 1972.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gory Killing of '72 Solved, Sources Say Arrests Sought In Case That Obsessed Police |author= |first=Robert J. |last=Terry |authorlink= |author2= |author3= |author4= |author5= |author6= |author7= |url= |format= |agency= |newspaper=Philadelphia Inquirer |publisher= |location= |isbn= |issn= |oclc= |pmid= |pmd= |bibcode= |doi= |id= |date=July 10, 1996 |page= |pages= |at= |accessdate= |language= |trans-title=|quote= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |ref= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mauryzlevy.wordpress.com/2011/02/02/dead-end-at-toms-river-a-bizarre-murder-mystery/|title=Dead End at Toms River: A Bizarre Murder Mystery|date=2011-02-02|website=Maury Z. Levy: Greatest Hits, Volume One|access-date=2017-04-25}}</ref>
==Disappearance== Shortly before midnight on July 11, 1972, Della Penna was abducted from her home in Philadelphia. Witnesses later informed the police that they had seen her beaten and dragged, while she was unconscious, into a car. Della Penna's [[torso]] and arms were later located in [[Jackson Township, New Jersey]]. Her legs were found in adjacent [[Manchester Township, New Jersey]]. Her head was never recovered and her murder remains unsolved.
== Investigation and aftermath == Her fingertips had been severed from her hands to prevent the police from identifying her. Their reports state that Della Penna was killed by drug dealers who thought that her boyfriend had stolen drugs from them. The crime remains unsolved, and is hotly debated online.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mja--inc--investigations.webs.com/apps/blog/show/44272039-unsolved-homicides-missing-person-cases|title=UNSOLVED HOMICIDES & MISSING PERSON CASES|website=Missing Persons & Unsolved Crimes & Doe's|access-date=2017-04-27}}</ref>
